      <memberdef kind="function" id="class_i2c_bus_1a02fd73d861ef2e4aabb38c0c9ff82947" prot="public" static="no" const="no" explicit="no" inline="no" virt="non-virtual">
        <type>void</type>
        <definition>void init</definition>
        <argsstring>()</argsstring>
        <name>init</name>
        <briefdescription>
<para>The init function. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para><hruler/>
</para>
<para>In case initialization still has been performed, indicated by flag init_done the function returns immediately, otherwise the I<superscript>2</superscript>C controller device structure will be retrieved by calling macro DEVICE_DT_GET and function checks if the device is ready for usage with call of function device_is_ready. The configuration bit mask is assigned to the device by calling function i2c_configure provided by the Zephyr device driver API. The return value rc of this function, combined with the return value of function device_is_ready by logical AND will be assigned to flag device_good. In case of an error a debug message at error level will be printed. Finally init_done flag is set to true. </para>
        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
        </inbodydescription>
