    <briefdescription>
<para>I<superscript>2</superscript>C bus driver class implemented according to C++ singleton design pattern. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para><hruler/>
</para>
<para><simplesect kind="par"><title>Detailed Description </title><para>The I<superscript>2</superscript>C bus class handles the initialization of the attached I<superscript>2</superscript>C slaves and the communication over the I<superscript>2</superscript>C bus. Major part of configuration and initialization is located in the device tree, other parts are located in the init function of this class. storage of the acceleration raw See details in <ulink url="https://docs.zephyrproject.org/latest/kernel/drivers/index.html">Device Driver Model documentation</ulink> and in <ulink url="https://docs.zephyrproject.org/apidoc/latest/group__i2c__interface.html">API documentation</ulink> <linebreak/>
 The <ref refid="class_i2c_bus" kindref="compound">I2cBus</ref> class provides the init method. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
    </detaileddescription>
